        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 2:20PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong line of
thunderstorms that extends from Burleson County through Brazos,
northwest Waller, and western Madison counties. Strong winds and
hail are possible in this line. We continue to monitor these storms
in this region for possible strengthening.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
College Station, Bryan, Madisonville, Caldwell, Snook, Kurten, Wixon
Valley, Lake Somerville State Park &amp; Trailway, Kyle Field, Bryan
Utilities Lake, Normangee, Iola, Lyons, Deanville, Chriesman, North
Zulch, and Wellborn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
